TUT announced its first annual fundraising golf day and prize-giving gala dinner scheduled at the Mbombela Golf Club at the end of June. The purpose of the event, TUT said, is to raise funds to support middle students not funded by NSFAS. The funds raised will go towards students in need of laptops, books, bursaries, accommodation and food.  Date: Thursday, June 30 Venue: Mbombela Golf Club Registration: 08:00 for 08:30 Tee-off: Shotgun at 09:00 Format: Four-ball alliance â€“ two scores to count scramble drive Entry fee: R4 000 per four-ball (includes green fees, golf carts, halfway house, prize-giving function) Sponsorships, co-branding and naming rights: R75 000 Branding and advertising at the gala dinner/prize-giving: R6 000 Purchasing a hole for advertising purposes: R3 500 Banner at the tee-off or water holes: R3 000 Website address: https://www.tut.ac.za/whats-on/events/event?NID=146 RSVP: https://forms.gle/4HJQTmjzo2CwahRj7 Armstrong Khumalo: 012 382 5346/khumalona1@tut.ac.za Thulani Ngathi: 012 382 5700/Ngathipt@tut.ac.za